### **2. Explain your project architecture (Monolithic vs Microservices)**

| Feature            | Monolithic                       | Microservices                                   |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| Codebase           | Single, large codebase           | Multiple small services                         |
| Deployment         | Single deployment                | Independent deployment per service              |
| Scalability        | Vertical scaling (CPU/RAM)       | Horizontal scaling per service                  |
| Fault Isolation    | Low                              | High — one service failure doesn’t crash system |
| Development Speed  | Slower for large teams           | Faster — teams work independently               |
| Example in Banking | Core banking platform in one app | Separate services: `Loan`, `Account`, `Payment` |

**Example:**

* **Monolithic:** Traditional bank app with all modules in one WAR/JAR.
* **Microservices:** Modern banking platform with separate services for payments, accounts, and transactions, deployed independently in Kubernetes.

